### Summary
- Overview: Gold is in a structurally bullish phase over the next three months, driven by persistent expectations of U.S. Federal Reserve rate cuts, a weakening U.S. dollar, and escalating geopolitical and economic instability. Repeated signals across articles highlight central bank demand, de-dollarization trends (especially among BRICS and Global South nations), and safe-haven flows amid U.S. fiscal deterioration and political interference in monetary policy. While short-term profit-taking and temporary dollar strength have triggered sharp pullbacks—such as the 5% drop in late October—these are viewed as buying opportunities rather than trend reversals. The co-movement of gold with Bitcoin and silver underscores a broad-based loss of confidence in fiat systems, reinforcing the bullish macro backdrop despite near-term volatility.

