- Overview: Gold is on a strong bullish trajectory over the next three months, driven by persistent safe-haven demand amid escalating geopolitical tensions, trade wars, and growing skepticism about the U.S. dollar’s reserve status. Anticipation of Federal Reserve rate cuts—spurred by weak U.S. economic data—continues to weaken the dollar, further boosting gold’s appeal. Central bank buying, especially from the Global South, is reinforcing structural demand, while political turmoil, including Trump’s aggressive tariff policies and attacks on Fed independence, is amplifying market uncertainty. Although short-term profit-taking may cause volatility, the macro backdrop remains strongly supportive. Key risks include a sudden hawkish pivot by the Fed or a de-escalation in trade tensions, which could temporarily dampen momentum.

